018package org.tquadrat.foundation.util.internal;
019
020import static java.util.Collections.emptySet;
021import static org.apiguardian.api.API.Status.INTERNAL;
022import static org.tquadrat.foundation.lang.Objects.requireNonNullArgument;
023
024import java.util.Collection;
025import java.util.Map;
026import java.util.Set;
027import java.util.function.Consumer;
028import java.util.function.Supplier;
029
030import org.apiguardian.api.API;
031import org.tquadrat.foundation.annotation.ClassVersion;
032import org.tquadrat.foundation.lang.Lazy;
033import org.tquadrat.foundation.util.LazyMap;
034
035/**
036 *  The implementation for
037 *  {@link LazyMap}.
038 *
039 *  @extauthor Thomas Thrien - thomas.thrien@tquadrat.org
040 *  @version $Id: LazyMapImpl.java 820 2020-12-29 20:34:22Z tquadrat $
041 *  @since 0.0.5
042 *
043 *  @param <K> The type of keys maintained by this map
044 *  @param <V> The type of mapped values
045 *
046 *  @UMLGraph.link
047 */
048@SuppressWarnings( "preview" )
049@ClassVersion( sourceVersion = "$Id: LazyMapImpl.java 820 2020-12-29 20:34:22Z tquadrat $" )
050@API( status = INTERNAL, since = "0.0.5" )
051public sealed class LazyMapImpl<K,V> implements LazyMap<K,V>
052    permits LazySortedMapImpl
053{
054        /*------------*\
055    ====** Attributes **=======================================================
056        \*------------*/
057    /**
058     *  The holder for the real map.
059     */
060    private final Lazy<? extends Map<K,V>> m_Holder;
061
062    /**
063     *  The flag that indicates whether the provided supplier will put values
064     *  to the list on initialisation.
065     */
066    private final boolean m_SupplierPopulates;
067
068        /*--------------*\
069    ====** Constructors **=====================================================
070        \*--------------*/
071    /**
072     *  Creates a new {@code LazyMapImpl} instance.
073     *
074     *  @param  doPopulate  {@code true} if the provided supplier will put
075     *      values to the map on initialisation, {@code false} if will create
076     *      an empty map.
077     *  @param  supplier    The supplier that initialises the internal map for
078     *      this instance when it is first needed.
079     */
080    public LazyMapImpl( final boolean doPopulate, final Supplier<? extends Map<K,V>> supplier )
081    {
082        m_SupplierPopulates = doPopulate;
083        m_Holder = Lazy.use( supplier );
084    }   //  LazyMapImpl()
085
086    /**
087     *  Creates a new {@code LazyMapImpl} instance that is initialised with the
088     *  given value.
089     *
090     *  @param  value   The initialisation value.
091     */
092    public LazyMapImpl( final Map<K,V> value )
093    {
094        m_SupplierPopulates = true;
095        m_Holder = Lazy.of( value );
096    }   //  LazyMapImpl()
097
098        /*---------*\
099    ====** Methods **==========================================================
100        \*---------*/
101    /**
102     *  {@inheritDoc}
103     */
104    @Override
105    public final void clear()
106    {
107        if( m_SupplierPopulates ) init();
108        m_Holder.ifPresent( Map::clear );
109    }   //  clear()
110
111    /**
112     *  {@inheritDoc}
113     */
114    @Override
115    public final boolean containsKey( final Object key )
116    {
117        @SuppressWarnings( "unlikely-arg-type" )
118        final var retValue = (m_Holder.isPresent() || m_SupplierPopulates) && m_Holder.get().containsKey( key );
119
120        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
121        return retValue;
122    }   //  containsKey()
123
124    /**
125     *  {@inheritDoc}
126     */
127    @Override
128    public final boolean containsValue( final Object value )
129    {
130        @SuppressWarnings( "unlikely-arg-type" )
131        final var retValue = (m_Holder.isPresent() || m_SupplierPopulates) && m_Holder.get().containsValue( value );
132
133        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
134        return retValue;
135    }   //  containsValue()
136
137    /**
138     *  {@inheritDoc}
139     */
140    @Override
141    public final Set<Entry<K,V>> entrySet()
142    {
143        if( m_SupplierPopulates ) init();
144        @SuppressWarnings( "unchecked" )
145        final var retValue = m_Holder.map( Map::entrySet ).orElse( emptySet() );
146
147        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
148        return retValue;
149    }   //  entrySet()
150
151    /**
152     *  {@inheritDoc}
153     */
154    @SuppressWarnings( "rawtypes" )
155    @Override
156    public final boolean equals( final Object o )
157    {
158        var retValue = o == this;
159        if( !retValue && (o instanceof Map other) )
160        {
161            /*
162             * Collections are equal if their contents is equal. Refer to the
163             * respective Javadoc for equals().
164             */
165            if( isPresent() || m_SupplierPopulates )
166            {
167                retValue = m_Holder.get().equals( other );
168            }
169            else
170            {
171                retValue = other.isEmpty();
172            }
173        }
174
175        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
176        return retValue;
177    }   //  equals()
178
179    /**
180     *  {@inheritDoc}
181     */
182    @Override
183    public final V get( final Object key )
184    {
185        if( m_SupplierPopulates ) init();
186        @SuppressWarnings( "unlikely-arg-type" )
187        final var retValue = m_Holder.map( m -> m.get( key ) ).orElse( null );
188
189        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
190        return retValue;
191    }   //  get()
192
193    /**
194     *  {@inheritDoc}
195     */
196    @Override
197    public final int hashCode() { return m_Holder.hashCode(); }
198
199    /**
200     *  Gives access to the internal
201     *  {@link Lazy}
202     *  instance for derived classes.
203     *
204     *  @return A reference to
205     *      {@link #m_Holder}.
206     */
207    /*
208     * Not final, because it will be overridden by LazySortedMap.
209     */
210    protected Lazy<? extends Map<K,V>> holder() { return m_Holder; }
211
212    /**
213     *  {@inheritDoc}
214     */
215    @Override
216    public void ifPresent( final Consumer<? super Map<K,V>> consumer )
217    {
218        //noinspection FunctionalExpressionCanBeFolded
219        m_Holder.ifPresent( requireNonNullArgument( consumer, "consumer" )::accept );
220    }   //  ifPresent()
221
222    /**
223     *  {@inheritDoc}
224     */
225    @Override
226    public final void init() { m_Holder.get(); }
227
228    /**
229     *  {@inheritDoc}
230     */
231    @Override
232    public final boolean isEmpty()
233    {
234        final var retValue = (!m_Holder.isPresent() && !m_SupplierPopulates) || m_Holder.get().isEmpty();
235
236        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
237        return retValue;
238    }   //  isEmpty()
239
240    /**
241     *  {@inheritDoc}
242     */
243    @Override
244    public final boolean isPresent() { return m_Holder.isPresent(); }
245
246    /**
247     *  {@inheritDoc}
248     */
249    @Override
250    public final Set<K> keySet()
251    {
252        if( m_SupplierPopulates ) init();
253        @SuppressWarnings( "unchecked" )
254        final var retValue = m_Holder.map( Map::keySet ).orElse( emptySet() );
255
256        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
257        return retValue;
258    }   //  keySet()
259
260    /**
261     *  {@inheritDoc}
262     */
263    @Override
264    public final V put( final K key, final V value )
265    {
266        final var retValue = m_Holder.get().put( key, value );
267
268        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
269        return retValue;
270    }   //  put()
271
272    /**
273     *  {@inheritDoc}
274     */
275    @Override
276    public final void putAll( final Map<? extends K,? extends V> map ) { m_Holder.get().putAll( map ); }
277
278    /**
279     *  {@inheritDoc}
280     */
281    @Override
282    public final V remove( final Object key )
283    {
284        if( m_SupplierPopulates ) init();
285        @SuppressWarnings( "unlikely-arg-type" )
286        final var retValue = m_Holder.map( m -> m.remove( key ) ).orElse( null );
287
288        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
289        return retValue;
290    }   //  remove()
291
292    /**
293     *  {@inheritDoc}
294     */
295    @Override
296    public final int size()
297    {
298        final var retValue = m_Holder.isPresent() || m_SupplierPopulates ? m_Holder.get().size() : 0;
299
300        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
301        return retValue;
302    }   //  size()
303
304    /**
305     *  {@inheritDoc}
306     */
307    @Override
308    public final String toString()
309    {
310        final var retValue = m_Holder.isPresent() || m_SupplierPopulates ? m_Holder.getAsString() : "[Not initialized]";
311
312        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
313        return retValue;
314    }   //  toString()
315
316    /**
317     *  {@inheritDoc}
318     */
319    @Override
320    public final Collection<V> values()
321    {
322        if( m_SupplierPopulates ) init();
323        @SuppressWarnings( "unchecked" )
324        final var retValue = m_Holder.map( Map::values ).orElse( emptySet() );
325
326        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
327        return retValue;
328    }   //  values()
329}
330//  class LazyMapImpl
331
